Alex Azar, the secretary of health and human services, admitted Wednesday that a vaccine for a new coronavirus might not be affordable for all Americans.
Exorbitant drug pricing often leaves life-saving treatment out of reach for the poorest Americans.
While Azar was leading the pharmaceutical giant, the cost of its drugs went up significantly.
